snippet.textDisplay: I loved Kobe and frankly, I'm still having a hard time with this.  Kobe = Greatness on and off the court.  Kobe in my mind is a god and I will never forget his spirit, smile, attitude, work ethic, intelligence, wisdom, athleticism, and candor.  Kobe gave back to the community in various ways especially after retirement. The Mamba School is a good example.  In 2010, I named my Shiba Inu dog, Kobe.  I had seen something great in a person and adored the name.  Nobody would argure that Kobe was perhaps the best in the game but as a person as a whole, just simply magnificent.  You will be missed brother Kobe because you touched the hearts of so many.
